  "text": "## Grafana Query Result Cache Implementation\n\nGrafana implements a comprehensive query result caching layer in the `pkg/services/caching` package that provides an abstraction over multiple cache backends. Here's a detailed breakdown of the architecture:\n\n### 1. Cache Service Interface and Abstraction\nThe core caching interface is defined in `pkg/services/caching/service.go` with the `CachingService` interface that supports:\n- `HandleQueryRequest()` - Checks cache for existing query results and returns an update function if cache miss\n- `HandleResourceRequest()` - Similar caching for resource requests\n\nThe OSS implementation (`OSSCachingService`) provides a no-op implementation, while the `CachingServiceClient` wraps this with request handling and metrics collection.\n\n### 2. Cache Key Generation\nCache keys are generated in `pkg/services/caching/service.go::GetKey()` using:\n- **Namespace and prefix support**: Keys are formatted as `namespace:prefix:hash`\n- **JSON Encoding**: The `JSONEncoder` struct encodes query objects to JSON using `json.NewEncoder()`\n- **SHA256 Hashing**: The `SHA256KeyFunc()` function creates a SHA256 hash of the encoded JSON, producing a consistent, collision-resistant key\n- The encoded key format ensures deterministic cache key generation for identical queries\n\n### 3. Cache Backend Abstraction (Redis, Memcached, In-Memory)\nThe remote cache abstraction is implemented in `pkg/infra/remotecache/` with:\n\n**RemoteCache Interface** (`remotecache.go`):\n- `CacheStorage` interface defines Get/Set/Delete operations for byte arrays\n- Supports configurable backends via `RemoteCacheSettings` configuration\n\n**Backend Implementations**:\n- **Redis** (`redis_storage.go`): Redis client-based distributed caching\n- **Memcached** (`memcached_storage.go`): Memcached protocol support\n- **Database** (`database_storage.go`): SQL database-backed caching for single-instance deployments\n- **Local In-Memory** (`pkg/infra/localcache/cache.go`): Go-cache based local caching with configurable TTL and cleanup intervals\n\n**Decorator Pattern**:\n- `prefixCacheStorage`: Adds a prefix to all cache keys\n- `encryptedCacheStorage`: Wraps cache values with encryption/decryption using the secrets service\n\n### 4. Cache TTL Policy\nTTL (Time-To-Live) policies are implemented through:\n- **Default TTL**: 24 hours (`defaultMaxCacheExpiration`) in `remotecache.go` when not specified\n- **Query-Specific TTL**: Set via `time.Duration` parameter in `cache.Set()` calls\n- **Configuration**: Defined in `pkg/setting/setting.go` and `pkg/plugins/models.go::QueryCachingConfig`\n- **QueryCachingConfig struct**: Contains `Enabled` boolean and `TTLMS` (milliseconds) for datasource-specific caching\n- **Panel-Level Override**: The `queryCachingTTL` field in dashboard panel queries allows per-query TTL overrides\n\n### 5. Cache Invalidation on Dashboard Save\nCache invalidation follows these patterns:\n- **Delete Operations**: Cache items are removed via `CacheStorage.Delete(ctx context.Context, key string) error`\n- **Metrics Tracking**: `pkg/services/caching/metrics.go` tracks cache operations with Prometheus histograms:\n  - `query_caching_request_duration_seconds` - Query cache performance\n  - `resource_caching_request_duration_seconds` - Resource cache performance\n- **Cache Status Headers**: X-Cache header set to HIT/MISS/BYPASS/ERROR/DISABLED values\n- **Event-Based Invalidation**: Dashboard save events trigger cache invalidation through event bus listeners (Enterprise feature)\n\n### 6. Request Flow and Integration\n**Query Execution Path** (`service.go::WithQueryDataCaching`):\n1. CachingServiceClient receives a QueryDataRequest\n2. Calls `HandleQueryRequest()` to check cache\n3. If cache hit: returns cached response\n4. If cache miss: executes query via provided function\n5. Updates cache with result via `UpdateCacheFn` callback\n6. Sets X-Cache response header with status\n7. Records metrics for performance monitoring\n\n**Response Caching**:\n- Type: `CachedQueryDataResponse` contains the cached response and an `UpdateCacheFn` callback\n- Conditional Caching: Uses feature flag `FlagAwsAsyncQueryCaching` to determine when to cache async query results\n- Error Handling: Only caches successful responses (nil error)\n\n### 7. Configuration and Settings\nCache configuration is managed in:\n- `pkg/setting/setting.go`: RemoteCacheSettings for backend selection\n- `conf/defaults.ini` and `conf/sample.ini`: Configuration file templates\n- Supported backends: `redis`, `memcached`, `database`, `memory`\n- Encryption support: Optional cache value encryption via secrets service\n- Prefix support: Configurable key prefix for namespace isolation\n\n### 8. Testing Support\n- `pkg/services/caching/fake_caching_service.go`: Mock implementation for testing\n- `pkg/services/caching/service_test.go`: Unit tests covering caching behavior\n- Remote cache backends have dedicated test files (`*_test.go` and `*_integration_test.go`)\n\nThe architecture enables Grafana to efficiently cache query results across multiple datasources while supporting both single-instance deployments (local cache) and distributed deployments (Redis/Memcached), with enterprise features handling cache invalidation tied to dashboard lifecycle events."
}

